<p>
  <span class="nym">Monday</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Middle English</span> <i>Monday</i>, <i>Monenday</i>, from <span class="lang">Old English</span> <i>mōnandæġ</i> 'day of the moon'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>This name is part of a pattern of names in English deriving from the names of days.  Cf., e.g., <a class="nym" href="Loveday">Loveday</a>, <a class="nym" href="Pasca">Pasca</a>, <a class="nym" href="Tiffany">Tiffany</a>, etc.</p>
  
  


